Attention parents and guardians:
Rector Schools will be implementing 8 fully virtual days this school year. These days will be used to fully integrate our digital learning platform and to practice the system in the event that we need to go fully virtual for a period of time. The first virtual day will be September 8th. All students will be off campus for that day and no buses will run. We will still serve a grab and go breakfast and lunch for those who want to stop by and get them. Breakfast will be 8-8:30 and lunch will be 11-11:30. A full virtual day calendar will be posted later this month. If you have any questions, feel free to contact your building principal.

post_text: Due to an off-site positive covid-19 case, Rector schools has 8 students who will be considered close contacts and will have to quarantine for 14 days. Rector schools has followed the response protocol given by DESE and ADH. All facilities have been deep cleaned and sanitized to ensure safety for our students. The families of those students directly involved have been notified and given instructions on how to proceed. We will continue to resume regular activities within the school district and follow all safety protocol and guidelines. If any new information comes out, we will keep you all informed.

post_text: One of our Class of 2020!! Very proud of all of young adults who are starting the next chapters in their lives. Great job, Rileigh! #CougarNation
shared_text:
The Green House Cottages Of Belle Meade
June 26 at 10:25 AM ·

Meet Rileigh Smith!!
Rileigh is a Shahbaz at the Jackson House! She said, “I’ve always wanted to work in the medical field, so I decided to start as a C N A because they were offering a class at my school for free. I wasn’t sure that I was going to like it at first, but I absolutely love it now. The best part about working at the cottages is that you get to work with 12 elders versus 20+ at a traditional nursing home. You get to spend quality time with your elders while taking care of them. “Rileigh plans on starting college in the Fall to being working toward her RN while continuing to work at the cottages. Thank you Rileigh for all you do! We are thankful for you!

Rector, Piggott, and Corning and will turn on the football or baseball/softball lights Friday night, April 17th at 8:20 pm (20:20 military time) for 20 minutes, 20 seconds to honor the 2020 graduating Seniors and the 2020 spring sports who lost their seasons. post_text:
Parents and Students:

At this time, Rector School District will remain open. According to the Governor's Emergency Proclamation, the Governor, in coordination, with the Secretary of Health and the Secretary of Education, have the sole authority to close public school campuses across the state for reasons related to COVID-19.

We will continue to take directives from the Governor and the Arkansas Department of Health as we navigate the COVID-19 effect on Arkansas and our district and strive to keep the safety of our students and staff as our main priority.

We will continue to update the School district Facebook page and send out alerts as more information becomes available.

post_text: Congratulations to Rector senior, Parker Bucy! #CougarNation
shared_text:
A-State Alumni Association is with Audrey Lott Poff and Tara Townsend Thomason.
March 12 at 12:19 PM ·

Because of Arkansans who have purchased the #License2Howl plate, these 7 seniors from around the state now have a reason to HOWL. They are the recipients of the 2020 License2HOWL scholarship and will join the pack at #AState in the fall! Pictured from left to right are: Parker Bucy of Rector HS, Halie Holt of Trumann HS, CLaire McCord of Nettleton HS, Seth Prunty of Cabot HS, Damon Rice of Fordyce HS, Sophie Watkins of Jonesboro HS, and Anna Young of Little Rock Christian Academy. These students were selected out of hundreds of applicants from across the state and will each receive the yearly $5,000 award from the scholarship awarded through #AStateAlumniAssociation. Congratulations! #PackPride #License2HOWL.

post_text: Congratulations to RHS Cougars of the month for February, Ben Owens and Paige Butler. One teacher said of Ben, “Ben is a dependable young man who is always willing to lend a hand, not only at school, but in the community as well.” Another teacher said of Paige, “She is kind, hardworking, and extremely talented. She represents our school in everything she does. We are lucky to have her.” We also want to thank Keith Hill and Shannon Haywood from Rector Downtown Drug for their continued support of our students. #CougarNation
